revision.text:
The '''Brattleboro Free Folk Festival''' is an American annual music festival which takes place in [[Brattleboro, Vermont]]. The festival began in 2003 and is considered part of the [[New Weird America]] music movement.<ref>{{cite news |title=Folk Music's New Genre Benders |author=Chris Dodge |url=http://www.utne.com/2004-03-01/FolkMusicsNewGenreBenders.aspx |magazine=[[Utne Reader]] |date=March–April 2004 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://pitchfork.com/features/articles/7174-it-still-moves/ |title=It Still Moves: Lost Songs, Lost Highways, and the Search for the Next American Music |author=[[Amanda Petrusich]] |date=25 August 2008 |work= |publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]] |accessdate=29 March 2012}}</ref>

