'''''Eqtesad-e Golestan''''' (اقتصاد گلستان lit. "Golestan Economics") is an [[Independent business|independent]] [[socio-economic]] [[Persian language]] weekly [[newspaper|paper]] published in Gorgan, [[Golestan Province|Golestan]], [[Iran]]. The first issue appeared on the newsstands throughout Golestan province and especially in the capital, Gorgan city, on 18 February 2005.

This is the fourteenth regular newspaper or magazine to be published in the province since 1996.

[[Moosa Jorjani]], a Sunni Muslim of the Iranian Turkomen ethnic minority origin, is its license holder and official director, and [[Abdonnasser Mohaimeni]], an Iranian Shii Muslim of Persian origin is its editor-in-chief and executive manager. At 22,500 copies for each issue, the newspaper has the largest circulation recorded in the history of local newspapers in North Iran.

''Eqtesad-e Golestan'' is usually published in eight (and sometimes twelve) pages, with the first and last pages being in full color. The size of each page is 35&nbsp;cm by 50&nbsp;cm.

At present, the newspaper is in no way a specialised one, but rather a general [[socio-cultural]] and economic weekly covering news, articles, commentaries and [[advertising|advertisement]]s related to local, national and international matters.

